import './Pokedex.scss' import { FontAwesomeIcon } from '@fortawesome/react-fontawesome' import { faCircleChevronRight, faCircleChevronLeft } from '@fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons' // don't need to take this test to know that I want to catch you :* // TODO: break into smaller components // TODO: add missing visual components function Pokedex ({leftScreenContent, pokemonHabitat, attributesScreenContent, changePokemon}) { const arrowRight = const arrowLeft = const habitat = pokemonHabitat; let leftScreenBG = ''; let leftScreenBGAriaLabel = ''; if (habitat === 'cave') { leftScreenBG = 'cave.jpg' leftScreenBGAriaLabel = 'Cave' } else if (habitat === 'forest' || habitat === 'grassland') { leftScreenBG = 'forest.jpg'; leftScreenBGAriaLabel = 'Forest' } else if (habitat === 'mountain') { leftScreenBG = 'mountain.jpg'; leftScreenBGAriaLabel = 'Mountain' } else if (habitat === 'rough-terrain') { leftScreenBG = 'rough-terrain.jpg'; leftScreenBGAriaLabel = 'Rough-terrain' } else if (habitat === 'sea') { leftScreenBG = 'sea.png'; leftScreenBGAriaLabel = 'Sea' } else if (habitat === 'urban') { leftScreenBG = 'urban.jpg'; leftScreenBGAriaLabel = 'Urban/city' } else { leftScreenBG = 'water-edges.jpg'; leftScreenBGAriaLabel = 'Water-edges' } return (
{leftScreenContent}
{attributesScreenContent}
); } export default Pokedex;
